org.sd.text.radixtree
Interface ValueReplicator<T>

public interface ValueReplicator<T>

An interface for duplicating an instance of a value for placement into nodes inserted for splits.

When a node is split, the existing node is inserted under a new node who shares the existing node's value before receiving a new child. Replicators are called to duplicate that value into the new node.

A replicator is not necessary for immutable values, but is essential for proper function with values that contain changing state, which is often the case with values that "merge".

Author:
Spence Koehler

Method Summary
 T replicate(T value)
          Replicate the given value to place in the new "parent" of a node containing the value created while splitting.
